{"IName_input":"Barrel of Sunset","IType_input":"component","WType_input":"","WDmg_input":"","Desc1_input":"This is a part of the legendary Sunset rifle, a fabled weapon forged long ago as a tool for wielding light against the darkness. Also known as 'radiant piercer', it did greater damage the further the targets alignment was from lawful good.","Desc2_input":"The Sunset was last rumoured to have been wielded by a great elven hero Alaine Greenleaf, but was feared too powerful and split into three pieces.","Desc3_input":"This is the barrel, a golden tube of metal with a strange spiked decoration, engraved on the side of the barrel is the word Sunset'. The barrel has clear rifling on the inside and the faint residual smell of gunpowder, but its safe to say this weapon has not be together for many hundreds of years.","Source_input":"Homebrew."}